Question for past rOpenSci unconf participants:

What was the most surprising thing about participating in an rOpenSci unconference? (asked by a 1st-timer today)

#runconf17 #runconf18
@ma_salmon @JennyBryan @lorenzwalthert Next week: How much work is onboarding?
@ma_salmon @JennyBryan @lorenzwalthert This series builds on the #satRdayCapeTown talk given by @ma_salmon. See her slides at https://t.co/K9fgtecWTV & the recording at https://t.co/jMWP5uKv0x

@ma_salmon @JennyBryan Packages used include rOpenSci's 
1. ghql to interact with GitHub V4 API
2. jqr to wrangle JSON
3. git2r to clone git repositories 
4. @lorenzwalthert's gitsum package to summarize git activity
@ma_salmon The 1st post presents onboarding data extraction from GitHub & git repositories - "rectangling" - as coined by @JennyBryan https://t.co/lfBZgIOF78 #rstats
[blog] New #rstats series! Our package reviews in review: Introducing a 3-post series about software onboarding data, introduced in https://t.co/dusOOPo9ch by @ma_salmon  #rstats
